00:02:40.050 --> 00:02:41.220
so I'm gonna be talking a little bit

00:02:41.220 --> 00:02:44.760
about the Jews of Ukraine
up to the year 1648.

00:02:44.760 --> 00:02:46.290
I understand you guys came up

00:02:46.290 --> 00:02:48.960
to the Battle of Grunwald in 1410,

00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:51.060
so I'm gonna go a little bit beyond that

00:02:51.060 --> 00:02:53.460
because honestly, not a whole lot is known

00:02:53.460 --> 00:02:55.050
about the Jewish communities

00:02:55.050 --> 00:02:58.350
in this part of Eastern
Europe before then,

00:02:58.350 --> 00:02:59.700
and so we're gonna go through all this,

00:02:59.700 --> 00:03:01.863
and we're gonna come up to 1648.

00:03:03.720 --> 00:03:08.280
I assume, to this point,
you've really been learning

00:03:08.280 --> 00:03:12.750
about the story of
colonizers and the colonized.

00:03:12.750 --> 00:03:15.180
Colonizers being Lithuanians,

00:03:15.180 --> 00:03:19.080
and then Poles, which you're
just starting to get into,

00:03:19.080 --> 00:03:22.590
and the colonized being
Ukrainians in this part.

00:03:22.590 --> 00:03:25.530
What I would like to talk about today

00:03:25.530 --> 00:03:27.810
is a third very prominent group,

00:03:27.810 --> 00:03:29.460
and that's the Jewish community,

00:03:29.460 --> 00:03:31.737
which is neither one
of these things, right?

00:03:31.737 --> 00:03:35.070
The Jews constitute a diaspora group,

00:03:35.070 --> 00:03:39.510
meaning they're without
a homeland, so to speak.

00:03:39.510 --> 00:03:40.803
They're a guest,

00:03:41.670 --> 00:03:43.950
and they have to somehow mediate

00:03:43.950 --> 00:03:47.763
between these colonizers
and the colonized.

00:03:49.020 --> 00:03:52.140
There's certain advantages
to being a diaspora group,

00:03:52.140 --> 00:03:54.210
if you think about it.

00:03:54.210 --> 00:03:58.560
They have a pretty far-flung

00:03:58.560 --> 00:04:01.983
social and mercantile network.

00:04:02.880 --> 00:04:04.320
They speak their own language

00:04:04.320 --> 00:04:05.760
and are able to cultivate,

00:04:05.760 --> 00:04:09.150
you know, an elite culture

00:04:09.150 --> 00:04:11.103
or subculture in these parts,

00:04:12.600 --> 00:04:14.313
and, you know,

00:04:16.440 --> 00:04:18.480
it's a situation of

00:04:18.480 --> 00:04:21.120
where they're able to
obtain economic niches

00:04:21.120 --> 00:04:23.070
and have a great deal of mobility.

00:04:23.070 --> 00:04:25.020
Those things are true.

00:04:25.020 --> 00:04:29.550
However, it's also a situation
of physical vulnerability.

00:04:29.550 --> 00:04:32.970
The Jews are members of a,

00:04:32.970 --> 00:04:36.330
well, ostensibly problematic religion,

00:04:36.330 --> 00:04:39.540
and, you know, as a result of this,

00:04:39.540 --> 00:04:43.740
they really wind up serving
the more powerful groups,

00:04:43.740 --> 00:04:47.643
meaning the Lithuanian
and the Polish colonizers,

00:04:48.540 --> 00:04:50.170
and this works out for a while

00:04:51.420 --> 00:04:55.260
until they really pay a
horrible price for this,

00:04:55.260 --> 00:04:56.820
you know, because Ukrainians

00:04:56.820 --> 00:04:59.790
are gonna rise up under Chmielnicki,

00:04:59.790 --> 00:05:03.870
and Chmielnicki is an anticolonial hero

00:05:03.870 --> 00:05:05.640
from a Ukrainian perspective,

00:05:05.640 --> 00:05:07.140
but from a Jewish perspective,

00:05:07.140 --> 00:05:10.230
after a series of horrific massacres,

00:05:10.230 --> 00:05:15.230
you know, Chmielnicki, for
them, is a vicious persecutor,

00:05:15.480 --> 00:05:19.083
and this is kind of the
price that they pay.

00:05:20.400 --> 00:05:23.800
I wanna start with the bad news

00:05:24.870 --> 00:05:27.360
and then move on to better news.

00:05:27.360 --> 00:05:30.360
The bad news is Jews, as
you probably figured out,

00:05:30.360 --> 00:05:31.833
are a pariah group,

00:05:32.670 --> 00:05:35.130
as some of the things
I mentioned indicate,

00:05:35.130 --> 00:05:37.863
and that has very deep roots here.

00:05:39.090 --> 00:05:43.020
It goes all the way back, in
fact, to early church fathers.

00:05:43.020 --> 00:05:44.100
The most benign,

00:05:44.100 --> 00:05:48.810
and, I would say, the formula
that's basically adopted

00:05:48.810 --> 00:05:52.560
throughout most of real everyday life

00:05:52.560 --> 00:05:54.210
is probably that one

00:05:54.210 --> 00:05:57.810
that's attributable to Augustine, okay?

00:05:57.810 --> 00:05:59.560
And we'll go into that in a minute,

00:06:00.450 --> 00:06:03.960
but first, I just want
to address this image,

00:06:03.960 --> 00:06:06.270
which, if you can make it out,

00:06:06.270 --> 00:06:08.970
is really a kind of image of ambivalence

00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:11.850
because over here on this side

00:06:11.850 --> 00:06:15.300
you have Jewish merchants, traders.

00:06:15.300 --> 00:06:18.120
They don't look very prosperous.

00:06:18.120 --> 00:06:22.020
On the other side, you have
peasants in their holiday garb,

00:06:22.020 --> 00:06:24.717
and the painter is called (indistinct),

00:06:25.890 --> 00:06:29.430
who would paint Polish and
Ukrainian kind of everyday life,

00:06:29.430 --> 00:06:34.143
landscapes, and depict sort
of scenes of everyday life.

00:06:35.190 --> 00:06:36.210
They're together.

00:06:36.210 --> 00:06:38.223
They're gathered in front of a tavern,

00:06:39.660 --> 00:06:42.390
but you can tell they're
pretty apart, right?

00:06:42.390 --> 00:06:46.140
They're divided by their dress.

00:06:46.140 --> 00:06:48.240
They're divided by their language.

00:06:48.240 --> 00:06:51.483
You know, Jews are speaking
Yiddish, predominantly,

00:06:52.560 --> 00:06:55.230
and the peasants have
their own local dialect.

00:06:55.230 --> 00:06:56.970
It's gonna be a Slavic language,

00:06:56.970 --> 00:07:00.483
and there's little kind of
communication between them.

00:07:01.650 --> 00:07:04.860
The Jews are also involved
in very different activity,

00:07:04.860 --> 00:07:07.920
you know, as traders, as petty merchants,

00:07:07.920 --> 00:07:10.920
compared to the peasants who,
on their holiday are dancing,

00:07:10.920 --> 00:07:13.350
and they're enjoying
themselves, probably drinking,

00:07:13.350 --> 00:07:15.690
and inside, if we went in there,

00:07:15.690 --> 00:07:18.123
we would probably see
a Jewish tavernkeeper.

00:07:19.050 --> 00:07:23.250
Jews leased taverns and
distilleries from the nobility.

00:07:23.250 --> 00:07:25.650
The vast majority of
taverns and distilleries

00:07:25.650 --> 00:07:30.000
throughout these regions
were actually run by Jews,

00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:33.750
and you really have
sort of a, I would say,

00:07:33.750 --> 00:07:36.330
an interaction, but not
an integration, right?

00:07:36.330 --> 00:07:38.130
An interaction within

00:07:38.130 --> 00:07:43.130
very prescribed social categories.

00:07:43.500 --> 00:07:45.090
You can call it a symbiosis

00:07:45.090 --> 00:07:48.960
because Jews are providing
essential services,

00:07:48.960 --> 00:07:51.450
the peasants providing
essential services to them,

00:07:51.450 --> 00:07:54.720
but, of course, it can also
develop into real animosity,

00:07:54.720 --> 00:07:58.200
misunderstanding, resentment,
and outright violence,

00:07:58.200 --> 00:08:02.193
so that's why I would call it
a situation of ambivalence.

00:08:03.780 --> 00:08:06.060
Where does the pariah status come from?

00:08:06.060 --> 00:08:07.620
If we go back to Augustine,

00:08:07.620 --> 00:08:11.100
I'd like to look at this text very closely

00:08:11.100 --> 00:08:13.383
because it looks like anti-Semitism,

00:08:14.340 --> 00:08:17.043
but it's not really intended to be so.

00:08:18.120 --> 00:08:20.347
This is from his "Contra Faustum":

00:08:20.347 --> 00:08:23.917
"It is not, as you say,
not by bodily death

00:08:23.917 --> 00:08:28.110
"shall the ungodly race
of carnal Jews perish,"

00:08:28.110 --> 00:08:32.205
and what he's basically
saying is you can't kill Jews.

00:08:32.205 --> 00:08:34.770
You know, they may have rejected Christ,

00:08:34.770 --> 00:08:36.090
but they live among us,

00:08:36.090 --> 00:08:37.920
and they're not to be harmed bodily,

00:08:37.920 --> 00:08:40.020
and this is in a context

00:08:40.020 --> 00:08:43.230
of forced conversions at this time period,

00:08:43.230 --> 00:08:45.780
you know, outright violence and death,

00:08:45.780 --> 00:08:49.290
and so he's really
actually proscribing this.

00:08:49.290 --> 00:08:52.747
He's forbidding this kind of thing.

00:08:52.747 --> 00:08:54.697
"For whoever destroys them in this way,

00:08:54.697 --> 00:08:57.660
"shall suffer sevenfold vengeance,"

00:08:57.660 --> 00:09:02.340
that is, shall bring upon
himself the sevenfold penalty

00:09:02.340 --> 00:09:06.870
under which the Jews lie for
the crucifixion of Christ,

00:09:06.870 --> 00:09:09.750
and so he is blaming Jews
for the death of Christ,

00:09:09.750 --> 00:09:11.280
and deicide,

00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:13.940
or at least the murder of
the human embodiment of God,

00:09:13.940 --> 00:09:16.293
is a pretty heavy penalty,

00:09:17.130 --> 00:09:19.500
so to the end of the seven days of time,

00:09:19.500 --> 00:09:22.350
the continued preservation of the Jews

00:09:22.350 --> 00:09:25.060
will be proof to believing Christians

00:09:26.010 --> 00:09:28.350
of the subjection merited

00:09:28.350 --> 00:09:31.020
by those who, in the
pride of their kingdom,

00:09:31.020 --> 00:09:32.763
put the Lord to death,

00:09:33.630 --> 00:09:37.740
and here is perhaps the most
dangerous formula of all

00:09:37.740 --> 00:09:40.410
because what it's basically saying is

00:09:40.410 --> 00:09:44.760
Jews are to be kept around
in a state of misery, right?

00:09:44.760 --> 00:09:48.540
As witness to what happens
when you reject Christ,

00:09:48.540 --> 00:09:50.073
but they're to be kept around.

00:09:51.060 --> 00:09:53.580
Now, the reason why I
consider this so dangerous is

00:09:53.580 --> 00:09:56.640
what happens when Jews
don't fulfill that role

00:09:56.640 --> 00:09:59.250
of misery, of subjection?

00:09:59.250 --> 00:10:00.630
What happens then?

00:10:00.630 --> 00:10:02.160
What happens when they're perceived

00:10:02.160 --> 00:10:05.040
as maybe violating that hierarchy,

00:10:05.040 --> 00:10:06.843
even subverting that hierarchy?

00:10:07.770 --> 00:10:12.060
And, of course, at the heart
of anti-Semitism is the claim

00:10:12.060 --> 00:10:16.320
of excessive Jewish power,
influence, and wealth,

00:10:16.320 --> 00:10:18.360
and all these things come into play,

00:10:18.360 --> 00:10:20.400
so what I'm asking is

00:10:20.400 --> 00:10:25.400
is this formula a license to kill

00:10:25.710 --> 00:10:28.140
when that, the Jewish part of the deal

00:10:28.140 --> 00:10:29.220
is not held up, right?

00:10:29.220 --> 00:10:31.983
The subjection or the misery,

00:10:33.120 --> 00:10:36.390
and, you know, I think
that kind of explains

00:10:36.390 --> 00:10:38.610
the trajectory that we're gonna follow.

00:10:38.610 --> 00:10:40.410
Most of the time,

00:10:40.410 --> 00:10:42.960
most of the time, Jews are gonna lead

00:10:42.960 --> 00:10:46.080
a relatively prosperous
and stable existence,

00:10:46.080 --> 00:10:47.610
but then there are these episodes,

00:10:47.610 --> 00:10:50.220
extremely violent devastating episodes,

00:10:50.220 --> 00:10:53.997
today, what we would call
genocide in some cases, you know,

00:10:55.480 --> 00:10:58.590
and, you know, are Jews
even aware of this bargain?

00:10:58.590 --> 00:11:00.090
Are they aware of this formula?

00:11:00.090 --> 00:11:02.400
It seems they are, to an extent,

00:11:02.400 --> 00:11:05.920
because rabbinical leaders
will actually forbid

00:11:08.376 --> 00:11:09.630
ostentatious display

00:11:09.630 --> 00:11:12.780
like jewelry and fancy clothing
and that kind of a thing,

00:11:12.780 --> 00:11:14.100
and they'll try very hard,

00:11:14.100 --> 00:11:16.450
but it's very hard to
control such things also.

00:11:17.910 --> 00:11:20.220
That being said, so
we've got this kind of,

00:11:20.220 --> 00:11:23.520
I would say, dangerous
balancing act, you know,

00:11:23.520 --> 00:11:27.390
and it's like a collective balancing act

00:11:27.390 --> 00:11:30.600
and this collective sense of ambivalence.

00:11:30.600 --> 00:11:31.953
That being said,

00:11:34.650 --> 00:11:37.980
most of the Jews of the world

00:11:37.980 --> 00:11:40.290
are going to move to
this part of the world,

00:11:40.290 --> 00:11:42.270
not all the Ukraine.

00:11:42.270 --> 00:11:44.370
It's gonna be, also, you know,

00:11:44.370 --> 00:11:48.000
the Polish kingdom and other
lands in Eastern Europe,

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:49.680
but it's pretty incredible.

00:11:49.680 --> 00:11:52.770
75% of the world's Jewish population

00:11:52.770 --> 00:11:56.943
is going to reside in Eastern
Europe by the 19th century,

00:11:58.650 --> 00:12:00.360
and there's a reason for that.

00:12:00.360 --> 00:12:02.370
It can't be that horrible
if they're living there.

00:12:02.370 --> 00:12:04.380
It certainly can't be that deadly.

00:12:04.380 --> 00:12:07.320
The reason for that is that stability

00:12:07.320 --> 00:12:10.020
and relative prosperity.

00:12:10.020 --> 00:12:12.360
They have economic autonomy.

00:12:12.360 --> 00:12:14.223
They're not allowed to own land,

00:12:15.300 --> 00:12:17.793
yet that can also be,

00:12:19.080 --> 00:12:21.330
I suppose, an advantage

00:12:21.330 --> 00:12:24.600
because they move into somewhat
more lucrative pursuits

00:12:24.600 --> 00:12:28.830
like trade, crafts, moneylending,

00:12:28.830 --> 00:12:30.990
and most importantly
all, as time develops,

00:12:30.990 --> 00:12:32.910
leaseholding from the nobility.

00:12:32.910 --> 00:12:35.537
They will lease pretty much all

00:12:35.537 --> 00:12:38.973
of the nonagricultural
enterprises of the nobles.

00:12:40.620 --> 00:12:41.973
Political autonomy.

00:12:42.840 --> 00:12:46.260
We're gonna see how they develop
virtually self-government.

00:12:46.260 --> 00:12:48.990
Now, later on, anti-Semitic
claims are gonna be

00:12:48.990 --> 00:12:51.330
that they constitute a
state within a state.

00:12:51.330 --> 00:12:52.980
I think that goes way too far.

00:12:52.980 --> 00:12:56.220
You know, it's all contingent
on the Polish landowners

00:12:56.220 --> 00:12:58.840
who own the vast majority
of land in these areas

00:13:00.240 --> 00:13:02.760
and linguistic autonomy.

00:13:02.760 --> 00:13:06.000
The vernacular everyday
language is Yiddish,

00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:08.490
a combination of German and Hebrew

00:13:08.490 --> 00:13:11.220
with some Slavic elements thrown in,

00:13:11.220 --> 00:13:15.330
and then Hebrew, which
functions a lot like Latin

00:13:15.330 --> 00:13:18.450
as an elite clerical
language, a literary language,

00:13:18.450 --> 00:13:21.663
one that's not really spoken
until the rise of Zionism.

00:13:26.940 --> 00:13:29.970
Now, we can go way back

00:13:29.970 --> 00:13:33.660
to the origins of Jewish presence

00:13:33.660 --> 00:13:36.540
in what becomes the Ukraine,

00:13:36.540 --> 00:13:40.650
but historians will often start

00:13:40.650 --> 00:13:43.440
with the Khazar kingdom,

00:13:43.440 --> 00:13:45.360
and it's kind of exciting to historians

00:13:45.360 --> 00:13:47.190
to think that there was a Jewish kingdom.

00:13:47.190 --> 00:13:50.100
Supposedly, the king converted to Judaism.

00:13:50.100 --> 00:13:52.230
There's a classic called the "Kuzari,"

00:13:52.230 --> 00:13:55.650
which tells this story how
the king had a representative

00:13:55.650 --> 00:13:58.260
from the Christians and
the Jews and the Muslims,

