who really experience this
in a negative way, obviously,

00:26:27.690 --> 00:26:30.900
and, you know, we have a volatile system,

00:26:30.900 --> 00:26:33.240
but it's held in place

00:26:33.240 --> 00:26:36.483
as long as the Polish
nobility is in power,

00:26:40.860 --> 00:26:42.000
and here's the thing.

00:26:42.000 --> 00:26:44.800
The nobility doesn't want the headache

00:26:45.780 --> 00:26:50.100
of collecting taxes
directly from these Jews.

00:26:50.100 --> 00:26:52.740
Plus, they can't be trusted to,

00:26:52.740 --> 00:26:54.030
you know, pay their taxes,

00:26:54.030 --> 00:26:55.830
and they all seem to have the same name,

00:26:55.830 --> 00:26:58.080
like Yitzchak ben Moshe and so on.

00:26:58.080 --> 00:27:00.150
You know, there's like
17 of them in one town,

00:27:00.150 --> 00:27:04.140
and so what they do is they
entrust the Jewish communities,

00:27:04.140 --> 00:27:06.900
first Jewish tax collectors, specifically,

00:27:06.900 --> 00:27:10.140
and then the kahals, which is
the Jewish self-government,

00:27:10.140 --> 00:27:12.990
to collect the taxes for them,

00:27:12.990 --> 00:27:17.220
and in the process,
they're giving the kahal...

00:27:17.220 --> 00:27:20.220
I guess you'd compare
it to a municipality.

00:27:20.220 --> 00:27:24.960
They're giving the kahals
complete autonomy, almost,

00:27:24.960 --> 00:27:28.080
to run daily affairs,

00:27:28.080 --> 00:27:32.610
to manage the garbage collection
and keep the streets clean

00:27:32.610 --> 00:27:33.750
and try to make sure

00:27:33.750 --> 00:27:37.080
people don't encroach
on each other's leases,

00:27:37.080 --> 00:27:40.143
and they manage the educational system,

00:27:41.550 --> 00:27:42.840
and they start to develop

00:27:42.840 --> 00:27:46.830
these extensive instruments of autonomy

00:27:46.830 --> 00:27:47.663
to the point where

00:27:47.663 --> 00:27:50.250
when there are disputes
between communities,

00:27:50.250 --> 00:27:52.143
they develop regional councils,

00:27:53.040 --> 00:27:55.380
and then, a real game changer

00:27:55.380 --> 00:27:58.447
is when the crown basically says,

00:27:58.447 --> 00:28:01.327
"Okay, we just want a lump
sum from you," you know?

00:28:01.327 --> 00:28:04.627
"Forget about the individual
communities collecting taxes.

00:28:04.627 --> 00:28:06.270
"Give us one lump sum,"

00:28:06.270 --> 00:28:10.500
and then the Grand Duchy of
Lithuania says the same thing,

00:28:10.500 --> 00:28:13.260
and that's when developing out of that

00:28:13.260 --> 00:28:15.210
is the Council of Four Lands,

00:28:15.210 --> 00:28:16.920
which is kind of like functioning

00:28:16.920 --> 00:28:20.760
as not just a supreme IRS,
a supreme tax collector,

00:28:20.760 --> 00:28:22.410
but a supreme court

00:28:22.410 --> 00:28:25.890
that's adjudicating disputes
between communities,

00:28:25.890 --> 00:28:29.370
that deals with, really, you
call them national problems,

00:28:29.370 --> 00:28:32.400
a blood libel accusation,
a ritual murder accusation,

00:28:32.400 --> 00:28:35.370
the accusation that Jews
have killed a Christian child

00:28:35.370 --> 00:28:37.410
and used their blood for their,

00:28:37.410 --> 00:28:39.210
used the blood for their rituals,

00:28:39.210 --> 00:28:41.490
which never happened, I should emphasize,

00:28:41.490 --> 00:28:44.400
but it was kind of like the
rumor that refused to go away

00:28:44.400 --> 00:28:48.630
because it symbolically
reenacts the crucifixion,

00:28:48.630 --> 00:28:50.733
and it has a lot of resonance that way,

00:28:51.570 --> 00:28:54.060
so, you know, this Council of Four Lands

00:28:54.060 --> 00:28:57.390
would have somebody intervene

00:28:57.390 --> 00:28:59.250
and try to prevent, you know,

00:28:59.250 --> 00:29:01.200
this thing from getting out of control.

00:29:01.200 --> 00:29:03.780
They would negotiate the taxes,

00:29:03.780 --> 00:29:08.040
and they would serve as a
supreme court in secular matters.

00:29:08.040 --> 00:29:11.460
Now, each kahal also
had a rabbinical court,

00:29:11.460 --> 00:29:15.420
so the entire Jewish community
is known as the kehila.

00:29:15.420 --> 00:29:17.460
It's run by the kahal,

00:29:17.460 --> 00:29:19.500
but they also have rabbis

00:29:19.500 --> 00:29:22.290
who are sort of separate from everything.

00:29:22.290 --> 00:29:26.310
That Council of Four
Lands is mainly merchants,

00:29:26.310 --> 00:29:30.540
is mainly wealthy merchants
and leaseholders, okay?

00:29:30.540 --> 00:29:32.460
The rabbis meet separately,

00:29:32.460 --> 00:29:35.160
and they tend to judge religious matters,

00:29:35.160 --> 00:29:36.270
which makes a lot of sense

00:29:36.270 --> 00:29:39.480
until you try to figure out
what a religious matter is.

00:29:39.480 --> 00:29:40.713
It's not so clear.

00:29:41.760 --> 00:29:44.160
Murder seems to be a religious matter.

00:29:44.160 --> 00:29:47.580
Theft, kind of, but it's
also a business matter,

00:29:47.580 --> 00:29:50.340
so there's a lot of, like,
jurisdictional disputes going on

00:29:50.340 --> 00:29:52.800
between rabbinical courts and lay courts,

00:29:52.800 --> 00:29:53.820
but by and large, you know,

00:29:53.820 --> 00:29:55.590
when things are functioning smoothly,

00:29:55.590 --> 00:29:57.180
they support each other,

00:29:57.180 --> 00:30:01.290
and there's a actual power

00:30:01.290 --> 00:30:03.030
to excommunicate members

00:30:03.030 --> 00:30:04.620
that's never really used,

00:30:04.620 --> 00:30:07.290
but the threat of
excommunication, called the herem,

00:30:07.290 --> 00:30:09.480
is enough to scare people

00:30:09.480 --> 00:30:13.230
into obeying the authority
of these various courts

00:30:13.230 --> 00:30:16.950
because being excommunicated
would really be truly horrible.

00:30:16.950 --> 00:30:19.020
You know, you would
really have no place to go

00:30:19.020 --> 00:30:21.840
in Christian society, in Jewish society,

00:30:21.840 --> 00:30:23.880
and it's like social death,

00:30:23.880 --> 00:30:27.990
and a really devastating
condition to be in.

00:30:27.990 --> 00:30:28.890
It's never used

00:30:28.890 --> 00:30:32.040
until the rise of the
false messianic movement

00:30:32.040 --> 00:30:34.890
of Shabbetai Tzvi, which happens later on.

00:30:34.890 --> 00:30:37.080
We'll maybe touch upon at the very end.

00:30:37.080 --> 00:30:40.590
Now, a shtadlan is a
very important function.

00:30:40.590 --> 00:30:43.080
The shtadlan is a lobbyist,

00:30:43.080 --> 00:30:44.970
and every community would have one.

00:30:44.970 --> 00:30:47.760
He speaks the language of the land.

00:30:47.760 --> 00:30:49.290
He knows the laws really well.

00:30:49.290 --> 00:30:50.670
He's charming

00:30:50.670 --> 00:30:54.360
and has somewhat of a secular education,

00:30:54.360 --> 00:30:57.060
so a lot of times doctors
would serve this purpose,

00:30:57.060 --> 00:31:00.030
and he basically is the go-between.

00:31:00.030 --> 00:31:01.830
You know, he'll talk to the authorities

00:31:01.830 --> 00:31:03.000
when something goes wrong,

00:31:03.000 --> 00:31:04.170
and this is kind of like,

00:31:04.170 --> 00:31:05.707
you know, Jewish foreign
policy, you could call it.

00:31:05.707 --> 00:31:08.640
You know, this is how they
defend their communities,

00:31:08.640 --> 00:31:12.660
through lobbying, yes,
through giving of bribes.

00:31:12.660 --> 00:31:14.910
I mean, this was actually
totally on the books,

00:31:14.910 --> 00:31:15.870
out in the open.

00:31:15.870 --> 00:31:17.850
It was a normal way of doing business.

00:31:17.850 --> 00:31:21.120
You bribed the secular officials
to protect your community,

00:31:21.120 --> 00:31:23.673
and no one seemed to see
anything wrong with that.

00:31:27.150 --> 00:31:30.060
Now, with this extensive autonomy,

00:31:30.060 --> 00:31:33.600
really, the most extensive
autonomy since antiquity,

00:31:33.600 --> 00:31:37.350
you also have the development
of vibrant religious life

00:31:37.350 --> 00:31:39.810
and the wooden synagogues.

00:31:39.810 --> 00:31:44.160
Here's one in Khodoriv in
the Ukrainian territories.

00:31:44.160 --> 00:31:48.270
They can develop very
ornate, beautiful artwork

00:31:48.270 --> 00:31:49.650
even though they're wooden synagogues,

00:31:49.650 --> 00:31:51.303
which suggests less wealth.

00:31:52.410 --> 00:31:54.900
Beautiful ceiling paintings.

00:31:54.900 --> 00:31:58.890
Down in the corner there,
I put an image of this guy,

00:31:58.890 --> 00:32:03.780
who's chained to the
synagogue wall outside

00:32:03.780 --> 00:32:05.370
by his neck.

00:32:05.370 --> 00:32:07.053
Any idea what he did wrong?

00:32:08.610 --> 00:32:10.113
He broke the Sabbath,

00:32:11.280 --> 00:32:13.890
so this is actually called the kuna,

00:32:13.890 --> 00:32:17.280
and I put it there to remind
us not to get too nostalgic

00:32:17.280 --> 00:32:19.620
about this flourishing religious life

00:32:19.620 --> 00:32:22.380
'cause there's a lot of religious
compulsion involved too.

00:32:22.380 --> 00:32:25.380
You know, keeping the
Sabbath was not a choice,

00:32:25.380 --> 00:32:28.140
at least not throughout
this period of time,

00:32:28.140 --> 00:32:30.270
and if you go to the town
of Czestochowa in Poland,

00:32:30.270 --> 00:32:32.460
you can actually see one of
these on the synagogue wall.

00:32:32.460 --> 00:32:33.663
It's pretty interesting.

00:32:34.500 --> 00:32:36.870
Most people could pay a fine
and get out of it, you know,

00:32:36.870 --> 00:32:38.610
and they would prefer to pay the fine

00:32:38.610 --> 00:32:40.740
than be publicly humiliated in this way,

00:32:40.740 --> 00:32:41.793
but it was there.

00:32:43.740 --> 00:32:46.530
Now, Jews are able to move into cities,

00:32:46.530 --> 00:32:49.770
but again, you come into direct conflict

00:32:49.770 --> 00:32:51.570
with the Christian townspeople,

00:32:51.570 --> 00:32:56.570
and economics is
something that's perceived

00:32:56.760 --> 00:32:58.410
in an ethnic way, right?

00:32:58.410 --> 00:33:03.410
There are groups against
groups, Christians against Jews,

00:33:03.690 --> 00:33:06.120
and the Christians manage to exact

00:33:06.120 --> 00:33:08.970
a lot of money and payment
from Jewish merchants,

00:33:08.970 --> 00:33:12.150
so it becomes very expensive
to do business in cities,

00:33:12.150 --> 00:33:15.660
and that's where your
leaseholding comes in,

00:33:15.660 --> 00:33:19.050
and the official word for lease is arenda.

00:33:19.050 --> 00:33:20.700
You may see it in your readings.

00:33:20.700 --> 00:33:23.970
The arenda can be a lease on
everything we've talked about

00:33:23.970 --> 00:33:28.800
and some things we didn't talk
about: tolls on roads, ponds.

00:33:28.800 --> 00:33:30.600
You can lease the tax,

00:33:30.600 --> 00:33:31.890
and then you get to keep anything

00:33:31.890 --> 00:33:34.410
over the amount that you collect.

00:33:34.410 --> 00:33:38.070
You can lease entire villages,
taverns, and distilleries.

00:33:38.070 --> 00:33:39.910
This is an absolute boon

00:33:41.130 --> 00:33:43.263
to Jews, economically,

00:33:44.700 --> 00:33:47.700
but let's just say it's
not good to be a serf

00:33:47.700 --> 00:33:49.380
in this situation,

00:33:49.380 --> 00:33:52.140
and the Polish-Lithuanian
Commonwealth comes to be known,

00:33:52.140 --> 00:33:54.090
as I don't know if
you've heard this before,

00:33:54.090 --> 00:33:56.160
heaven for the nobles,
paradise for the Jews,

00:33:56.160 --> 00:33:57.510
and hell for the serfs.

00:33:57.510 --> 00:34:00.600
The reason is this is an arrangement

00:34:00.600 --> 00:34:05.400
that is not only economically
debilitating for the serfs

00:34:05.400 --> 00:34:07.020
who have to continually work,

00:34:07.020 --> 00:34:09.450
you know, the nobleman's land for free

00:34:09.450 --> 00:34:11.760
along with whatever land they're
able to work of their own,

00:34:11.760 --> 00:34:13.680
which is very small.

00:34:13.680 --> 00:34:16.050
They have to, you know,

00:34:16.050 --> 00:34:19.620
pay the Jewish tavernkeeper.

00:34:19.620 --> 00:34:21.693
They have to pay the Jewish miller.

00:34:23.460 --> 00:34:26.580
There are even rumors that
Jews lease the churches

00:34:26.580 --> 00:34:28.620
and held keys to the churches,

00:34:28.620 --> 00:34:29.880
which would be really humiliating,

00:34:29.880 --> 00:34:32.880
but some historians have said
that's actually not the case,

00:34:32.880 --> 00:34:33.780
but that is something

00:34:33.780 --> 00:34:36.270
that made its way up
through Ukrainian lore

00:34:36.270 --> 00:34:38.700
is that you even had to
beg to use your own church,

00:34:38.700 --> 00:34:40.890
you know, so it's a really
humiliating situation,

00:34:40.890 --> 00:34:43.140
whether that last thing is true or not,

00:34:43.140 --> 00:34:46.140
and that's the reason for the volatility,

00:34:46.140 --> 00:34:49.890
but nobody's going to attack
the Jewish leaseholder

00:34:49.890 --> 00:34:51.420
for the simple reason

00:34:51.420 --> 00:34:54.360
that he's under the
protection of the nobleman.

00:34:54.360 --> 00:34:57.690
Nobles own the vast majority of land.

00:34:57.690 --> 00:35:00.150
They're increasingly more
powerful than the king,

00:35:00.150 --> 00:35:03.390
who becomes an elected monarch,

00:35:03.390 --> 00:35:07.230
and they really, I would say,

00:35:07.230 --> 00:35:08.760
they own their own towns,

00:35:08.760 --> 00:35:12.180
and those are increasingly
attractive to Jews to settle in.

00:35:12.180 --> 00:35:14.673
It's a system of patronage, really.

00:35:18.150 --> 00:35:20.163
Now, inside the tavern,

00:35:21.900 --> 00:35:25.470
you have that integration
that I was talking about,

00:35:25.470 --> 00:35:27.573
but it's really more of an interaction,

00:35:28.410 --> 00:35:31.050
and here you have Jewish musicians,

00:35:31.050 --> 00:35:33.000
non-Jews who are dancing,

00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:37.470
and you have the Jewish
tavernkeepers over on that side,

00:35:37.470 --> 00:35:42.470
and notice that the
wife of the tavernkeeper

00:35:43.080 --> 00:35:44.940
is pouring the liquor.

00:35:44.940 --> 00:35:47.820
I'm not sure whose child
that is in the corner there,

00:35:47.820 --> 00:35:49.860
but children were very much present

00:35:49.860 --> 00:35:51.990
in these taverns as well.

00:35:51.990 --> 00:35:54.750
This was where people would
spend their leisure time.

00:35:54.750 --> 00:35:58.530
These were also, effectively, news venues,

00:35:58.530 --> 00:36:02.430
entertainment venues,
banks, country stores,

00:36:02.430 --> 00:36:03.840
especially in the smaller,

00:36:03.840 --> 00:36:06.570
you know, rural areas or small towns.

00:36:06.570 --> 00:36:09.870
They were the hub of everything,

00:36:09.870 --> 00:36:11.460
competing, really, with the church,

00:36:11.460 --> 00:36:13.620
you know, because after the wedding,

00:36:13.620 --> 00:36:16.440
you would, you know, proceed
from the church to the tavern,

00:36:16.440 --> 00:36:17.970
where you'd be met by the tavernkeeper,

00:36:17.970 --> 00:36:20.430
who's kind of like the antipriest,

00:36:20.430 --> 00:36:22.170
but what I want to emphasize is gender

00:36:22.170 --> 00:36:27.150
because women worked in the
society, in Jewish society,

00:36:27.150 --> 00:36:29.220
and it was expected.

00:36:29.220 --> 00:36:31.620
It wasn't something that
women fought for as a right.

00:36:31.620 --> 00:36:33.540
It was absolutely expected.

00:36:33.540 --> 00:36:36.960
Your value on the marriage
market was determined

00:36:36.960 --> 00:36:40.773
by what business promise you
could bring to the marriage.

00:36:41.640 --> 00:36:43.050
That would often be linguistic,

00:36:43.050 --> 00:36:47.040
like, how well you speak Polish
or Ukrainian or whatever,

00:36:47.040 --> 00:36:48.900
how well you know arithmetic,

00:36:48.900 --> 00:36:53.670
and these marriages were
really business partnerships.

00:36:53.670 --> 00:36:56.460
Usually, the husband would be
dealing with the suppliers.

00:36:56.460 --> 00:36:58.020
He might drive a taxi,

00:36:58.020 --> 00:37:01.380
you know, a horse and
cart during the week.

00:37:01.380 --> 00:37:05.430
The woman would be, the wife
would be serving the customers,

00:37:05.430 --> 00:37:08.160
and it's a pretty rough lifestyle,

00:37:08.160 --> 00:37:10.590
but why that's important is

00:37:10.590 --> 00:37:12.390
the Jewish familial unit

00:37:12.390 --> 00:37:16.650
presents a kind of double-barrel
threat economically

00:37:16.650 --> 00:37:19.500
because both the husband
and wife are working,

00:37:19.500 --> 00:37:22.290
and this is absolutely the norm.

00:37:22.290 --> 00:37:24.360
Occasionally, you have the situation

00:37:24.360 --> 00:37:28.600
where an extremely learned
and accomplished rabbi

00:37:30.570 --> 00:37:32.610
would study all day long

00:37:32.610 --> 00:37:34.650
and the wife would work in the marketplace

00:37:34.650 --> 00:37:35.730
or in the tavern, whatever,

00:37:35.730 --> 00:37:39.303
but that was a pretty
rare occurrence, okay.

00:37:42.930 --> 00:37:45.150
Now, one arenda dispute

00:37:45.150 --> 00:37:48.600
that I went through pretty extensively

00:37:48.600 --> 00:37:51.450
illustrates the problem with authority,

00:37:51.450 --> 00:37:52.410
the way things stand,

00:37:52.410 --> 00:37:53.970
and the importance of the development

00:37:53.970 --> 00:37:56.700
of the Council of Four
Lands, that supreme court.

00:37:56.700 --> 00:37:58.950
I just wanna go through
this really quickly

00:37:58.950 --> 00:38:02.940
because what happens in
this situation of leases,

00:38:02.940 --> 00:38:05.610
and this is probably a
tavern that's being leased,

00:38:05.610 --> 00:38:08.910
is competition between Jews, okay?

00:38:08.910 --> 00:38:13.260
In this case, Simeon
leases a liquor arenda.

00:38:13.260 --> 00:38:15.930
Reuben attempts to purchase
it for the next three years

00:38:15.930 --> 00:38:19.290
before his term is up,
so he's the encroacher,

00:38:19.290 --> 00:38:22.140
and then, Simeon goes and negotiates

00:38:22.140 --> 00:38:25.260
with the local nobleman,
successfully, who gives it to him.

00:38:25.260 --> 00:38:28.590
Reuben, in this case, goes
all the way to the queen

00:38:28.590 --> 00:38:31.860
and gets her scribe to support his side,

00:38:31.860 --> 00:38:35.700
and he tells the town council
to award the lease to Reuben.

00:38:35.700 --> 00:38:37.170
The towns council agree,

00:38:37.170 --> 00:38:39.480
town council agrees, but for a bribe.

00:38:39.480 --> 00:38:40.950
Reuben pays the bribe.

00:38:40.950 --> 00:38:42.840
Simeon bribes the nobleman,

00:38:42.840 --> 00:38:44.730
so lots of bribes going on here,

00:38:44.730 --> 00:38:47.160
and offers an even higher price,

00:38:47.160 --> 00:38:49.890
and the nobleman orders the town council

00:38:49.890 --> 00:38:51.510
to withdraw it from Reuben,

00:38:51.510 --> 00:38:54.660
and then the queen steps
in and supports Reuben,

00:38:54.660 --> 00:38:56.070
so you have, like,

00:38:56.070 --> 00:38:59.340
these conflicting secular
authorities that get involved,

00:38:59.340 --> 00:39:01.260
which leads me to think it's
much more than a tavern.

00:39:01.260 --> 00:39:03.780
It could be, you know, an
entire right to distill,

00:39:03.780 --> 00:39:05.880
which is called (speaks
in foreign language),

00:39:05.880 --> 00:39:08.310
but it's something that
is pretty lucrative,

00:39:08.310 --> 00:39:10.710
so they actually don't
stop with the authorities,

00:39:10.710 --> 00:39:12.150
not even the queen.

00:39:12.150 --> 00:39:13.980
They now go to the rabbis,

00:39:13.980 --> 00:39:17.550
and the rabbis are extremely
prominent in this society,

00:39:17.550 --> 00:39:20.160
which is a, you know,
community of believers.

00:39:20.160 --> 00:39:22.560
Some of these rabbis
have their own yeshivas,

00:39:22.560 --> 00:39:24.510
these Talmudic academies,

00:39:24.510 --> 00:39:29.190
where they teach the Talmud all day long,

00:39:29.190 --> 00:39:32.430
but when disputes occur

00:39:32.430 --> 00:39:37.430
that have to do with some
aspect of Jewish law, halakha,

00:39:37.530 --> 00:39:40.920
they will often send questions
to the most prominent rabbis,

00:39:40.920 --> 00:39:43.710
and this is what happens in this case,

00:39:43.710 --> 00:39:47.943
so Rabbi Isaac Ben Bezalel of Volodymyr,

00:39:49.320 --> 00:39:51.690
he argues in favor of Simeon,

00:39:51.690 --> 00:39:55.050
and he quotes a medieval German source

00:39:55.050 --> 00:39:58.920
to basically say, "Do not encroach," okay?

00:39:58.920 --> 00:40:02.943
So he's basically anti-Reuben,
anti-encroachment,

00:40:05.040 --> 00:40:09.510
but then they go to a
more prominent rabbi,

00:40:09.510 --> 00:40:13.860
Isaac Luria, who's young, but
he's kind of a rising star,

00:40:13.860 --> 00:40:17.640
and he actually rules in favor of Reuben

00:40:17.640 --> 00:40:20.310
and says that the laws of
encroachment don't apply

00:40:20.310 --> 00:40:23.520
'cause this is only a
potential purchase, right?

00:40:23.520 --> 00:40:27.180
The lease term hadn't begun
yet, so it's a potential,

00:40:27.180 --> 00:40:29.700
it's like the next
three years of the term,

00:40:29.700 --> 00:40:32.647
and he says, "It's known
in the entire kingdom

00:40:32.647 --> 00:40:35.077
"that we buy the right
to farm taxes and liquor

00:40:35.077 --> 00:40:37.740
"and other rights in the town
with an arenda contract,"

00:40:37.740 --> 00:40:40.320
and they're also accustomed
to sell the arenda

00:40:40.320 --> 00:40:44.490
before the term for the first
holder of the arenda expires,

00:40:44.490 --> 00:40:47.610
and they sell it to a second
person, so Reuben's okay.

00:40:47.610 --> 00:40:49.740
He's allowed to encroach, okay?

00:40:49.740 --> 00:40:51.510
Now, Luria's young.

00:40:51.510 --> 00:40:54.690
He may be brilliant and a
rising star, but he's young,

00:40:54.690 --> 00:40:57.750
so he sends it to an
older rabbinic authority

00:40:57.750 --> 00:41:01.623
for a kind of second
opinion, just to make sure,

00:41:03.510 --> 00:41:07.320
and this guy, his name
is Rabbi Joseph Katz,

00:41:07.320 --> 00:41:10.440
and he rules, actually, against him

00:41:10.440 --> 00:41:11.820
and rules in favor of Simeon,

00:41:11.820 --> 00:41:14.040
so you see it's a whole mess.

00:41:14.040 --> 00:41:16.890
It's a jurisdictional nightmare,

00:41:16.890 --> 00:41:19.410
and he argues that the
laws of encroachment

00:41:19.410 --> 00:41:22.500
do apply to ownerless property,

00:41:22.500 --> 00:41:26.550
and only when there's a
complete public agreement

00:41:26.550 --> 00:41:28.710
can that law be abrogated,

00:41:28.710 --> 00:41:31.050
and we don't know how it's resolved,

00:41:31.050 --> 00:41:33.930
but we do know that about 50 years later,

00:41:33.930 --> 00:41:36.940
the Council of Four Lands
finally issues a ruling

00:41:38.310 --> 00:41:41.250
banning any Jew from bidding on an arenda

00:41:41.250 --> 00:41:43.410
that's held by a fellow Jew,

00:41:43.410 --> 00:41:47.670
and then, the Lithuanian
Council steps in and agrees.

00:41:47.670 --> 00:41:50.400
They reiterate the ban,
and they give a reason:

00:41:50.400 --> 00:41:54.690
Competitive bidding causes
damage to the Jewish community

00:41:54.690 --> 00:41:57.510
by raising the costs
of leasing the arenda,

00:41:57.510 --> 00:41:59.670
so now, with the Council of Four Lands,

00:41:59.670 --> 00:42:00.810
which began as, basically,

00:42:00.810 --> 00:42:04.380
a tax collecting, you know, institution,

00:42:04.380 --> 00:42:09.000
we actually have it regulating
daily life and economic law,

00:42:09.000 --> 00:42:13.470
and things start getting
more regulated, more normal,

00:42:13.470 --> 00:42:16.050
and more in favor

00:42:16.050 --> 00:42:18.723
of Jewish business practices,

00:42:21.330 --> 00:42:24.270
but there's a downside
to all this liquor sales.

00:42:24.270 --> 00:42:25.890
It may be lucrative,

00:42:25.890 --> 00:42:28.110
and that's why people
are fighting about it.

00:42:28.110 --> 00:42:30.330
Here's a much later depiction.

00:42:30.330 --> 00:42:34.230
You see a pretty satanic-looking
Jewish tavernkeeper

00:42:34.230 --> 00:42:36.360
who's looking on unconcerned

00:42:36.360 --> 00:42:39.690
as the peasants are drunk and passed out,

00:42:39.690 --> 00:42:43.770
and, you know, this is a
real problem, you know,

00:42:43.770 --> 00:42:47.550
and people begin to blame
peasant drunkenness on Jews,

00:42:47.550 --> 00:42:49.710
and they accuse the Jewish tavernkeeper

00:42:49.710 --> 00:42:52.560
of, you know, driving
up his drinking debts

00:42:52.560 --> 00:42:54.720
and taking advantage of the peasantry,

00:42:54.720 --> 00:42:59.720
and it causes a lot of social
instability as a result.

00:43:01.290 --> 00:43:04.710
Now, on the positive side of things,

00:43:04.710 --> 00:43:06.370
we know from rabbinic takkanot

00:43:07.350 --> 00:43:11.310
that non-Jews were also part of this thing

00:43:11.310 --> 00:43:14.850
and profiting from these arendas on liquor

00:43:14.850 --> 00:43:18.810
because you can't keep a
tavern running on the Sabbath

00:43:18.810 --> 00:43:19.860
if you're Jewish

00:43:19.860 --> 00:43:20.880
or on holidays,

00:43:20.880 --> 00:43:23.180
like we just had the
holiday of Rosh Hashanah.

00:43:24.090 --> 00:43:27.300
It's not lawful, so what do they do?

00:43:27.300 --> 00:43:30.540
They have local Christians

00:43:30.540 --> 00:43:35.160
helping them to run the
taverns on those days,

00:43:35.160 --> 00:43:37.500
and actually, it becomes
a formal partnership

00:43:37.500 --> 00:43:40.950
because that's legally,
halakh-ically, what you have to do,

00:43:40.950 --> 00:43:45.250
and so, really, you see a
surprising amount of cooperation

00:43:46.110 --> 00:43:48.930
and, you know, economic
integration going on

00:43:48.930 --> 00:43:50.520
at the local level

00:43:50.520 --> 00:43:52.890
where, if you really wanna spell it out,

00:43:52.890 --> 00:43:54.690
Christians are helping Jews

00:43:54.690 --> 00:43:58.080
to get around their own
Sabbath restrictions

00:43:58.080 --> 00:44:00.150
so that they can remain profitable

00:44:00.150 --> 00:44:02.430
and they're also making, you know,

00:44:02.430 --> 00:44:04.140
a fair amount of money doing so,

00:44:04.140 --> 00:44:07.590
so there's a fair amount
of cooperation going on.

00:44:07.590 --> 00:44:10.050
There are rabbis who are
against this practice,

00:44:10.050 --> 00:44:12.450
strenuously against it,

00:44:12.450 --> 00:44:16.860
and Rabbi Betzalel Darshan of Przemysl

00:44:16.860 --> 00:44:20.520
blames the 1648 massacres

00:44:20.520 --> 00:44:23.130
on this practice itself.

00:44:23.130 --> 00:44:24.750
How much time is left?

00:44:24.750 --> 00:44:25.583
- About 10 minutes.

00:44:25.583 --> 00:44:27.630
- 10 minutes, good, okay.
(student speaks faintly)

00:44:27.630 --> 00:44:29.010
Six minutes, okay,

00:44:29.010 --> 00:44:33.157
so yeah, in very emotional language,

00:44:33.157 --> 00:44:35.077
"The blood of fathers and sons,

00:44:35.077 --> 00:44:38.257
"the blood of pious men
and children, or women,

00:44:38.257 --> 00:44:40.417
"the blood of saintly men and women

00:44:40.417 --> 00:44:42.697
"and the blood of baby boys and girls

00:44:42.697 --> 00:44:44.857
"still suckling at their mother's breasts

00:44:44.857 --> 00:44:47.887
"who had never sinned or
committed," sorry, "any crime,

00:44:47.887 --> 00:44:50.377
"and the blood of rabbis
and their disciples

00:44:50.377 --> 00:44:52.230
"was spilled like water."

00:44:52.230 --> 00:44:55.050
This is the 1648 uprising,

00:44:55.050 --> 00:44:57.960
and Chmielnicki massacre
of the Jewish communities

00:44:57.960 --> 00:44:59.347
he's talking about.

00:44:59.347 --> 00:45:00.450
"God is righteous."

00:45:00.450 --> 00:45:02.640
We can't blame God for this,

00:45:02.640 --> 00:45:05.400
and notice he's not gonna
blame the Cossacks either.

00:45:05.400 --> 00:45:07.377
He's not gonna blame Chmielnicki.

00:45:07.377 --> 00:45:09.487
"It is we who are wicked

00:45:09.487 --> 00:45:12.937
"because of our repeated
desecrations of the Sabbath.

00:45:12.937 --> 00:45:14.737
"A select group,

00:45:14.737 --> 00:45:18.127
"the majority of villagers
who undertake arendas,

00:45:18.127 --> 00:45:22.657
"buy and sell on the Sabbath
through the agency of villagers

00:45:22.657 --> 00:45:24.810
"all in a deceitful manner."

00:45:24.810 --> 00:45:26.760
They also order their gentile servants

00:45:26.760 --> 00:45:27.937
to "do such and such work,

00:45:27.937 --> 00:45:28.987
"and they sit and teach them

00:45:28.987 --> 00:45:31.260
"how to repair what has spoiled the job."

00:45:31.260 --> 00:45:33.060
This has all happening on the Sabbath,

00:45:33.060 --> 00:45:34.170
and, of course,

00:45:34.170 --> 00:45:38.347
God has punished the entire
Jewish community for this.

00:45:38.347 --> 00:45:41.107
"Oy for my eyes, which
saw this many times,

00:45:41.107 --> 00:45:42.720
"and I had no way of protesting."

00:45:42.720 --> 00:45:45.097
Then he goes on, kind
of like a Jewish mother.

00:45:45.097 --> 00:45:48.720
"Now, you see what happens,
and maybe you'll listen to me,"

00:45:48.720 --> 00:45:50.940
and turns out nobody listens to him

00:45:50.940 --> 00:45:52.380
because this practice continues.

00:45:52.380 --> 00:45:54.060
It's the only way of running

00:45:54.060 --> 00:45:56.940
a lucrative tavern and distillery.

00:45:56.940 --> 00:46:00.360
In fact, rabbis get involved
in writing contracts up

00:46:00.360 --> 00:46:02.580
where they form fictitious partnerships,

00:46:02.580 --> 00:46:03.840
and the practice continues,

00:46:03.840 --> 00:46:06.520
but let me go back to
that Chmielnicki uprising

00:46:07.560 --> 00:46:11.730
because it's absolutely devastating,

00:46:11.730 --> 00:46:15.780
and yet I'm not gonna
condone massacres, obviously,

00:46:15.780 --> 00:46:17.010
but it's understandable

00:46:17.010 --> 00:46:19.590
the position of Cossacks and Ukrainians.

00:46:19.590 --> 00:46:21.030
Now, who are Cossacks?

00:46:21.030 --> 00:46:25.083
They're essentially
peasants who resist serfdom.

00:46:26.250 --> 00:46:28.860
They obtain horses and weaponry.

00:46:28.860 --> 00:46:32.370
They often will ride down
in the Zaporozhian district

00:46:32.370 --> 00:46:37.050
and make, carry out raids
on the Ottoman territories,

00:46:37.050 --> 00:46:40.050
and the Polish army tries to use them

00:46:40.050 --> 00:46:42.510
and register them in the Polish army,

00:46:42.510 --> 00:46:44.040
but then they try to
cut down their numbers,

00:46:44.040 --> 00:46:47.400
and there a series of Cossacks revolts

00:46:47.400 --> 00:46:50.883
against the Polish government,
Polish Lithuanian government,

00:46:51.870 --> 00:46:53.940
and in 1648,

00:46:53.940 --> 00:46:58.830
there's a major uprising
led by Chmielnicki,

00:46:58.830 --> 00:47:03.780
who's a semi-polonized Ukrainian nobleman

00:47:03.780 --> 00:47:05.160
who's been spurned.

00:47:05.160 --> 00:47:07.230
He fell in love with a daughter

00:47:07.230 --> 00:47:10.470
of very powerful wealthy Polish nobleman

00:47:10.470 --> 00:47:11.640
who threw him into jail,

00:47:11.640 --> 00:47:15.360
and he broke out and rode
down and fomented rebellion,

00:47:15.360 --> 00:47:17.880
and the rebellion...

00:47:17.880 --> 00:47:21.210
Look, I mean, if they could
reach the Polish nobility,

00:47:21.210 --> 00:47:24.330
they probably would've tried,

00:47:24.330 --> 00:47:25.530
but you can't reach them.

00:47:25.530 --> 00:47:26.520
They're too mobile.

00:47:26.520 --> 00:47:30.060
They're too powerful, and
so who do they attack?

00:47:30.060 --> 00:47:33.600
The perceived agents
of the Polish nobility,

00:47:33.600 --> 00:47:35.880
namely, the Jewish leaseholders

00:47:35.880 --> 00:47:37.740
and other Jews in their midst,

00:47:37.740 --> 00:47:41.220
and Jews are massacred in huge numbers

00:47:41.220 --> 00:47:43.050
and in very sadistic manners.

00:47:43.050 --> 00:47:47.190
I'm not gonna read because
it's absolutely horrific,

00:47:47.190 --> 00:47:50.100
and you wonder if there's like
a little bit of imagination

00:47:50.100 --> 00:47:51.750
going on in these chronicles.

00:47:51.750 --> 00:47:54.360
This is the famous one
by Nathan of Hanover,

00:47:54.360 --> 00:47:56.610
but let's just say it's gruesome,

00:47:56.610 --> 00:48:00.450
and a colleague of mine, Adam Teller,

00:48:00.450 --> 00:48:02.790
has found a Polish version of this

00:48:02.790 --> 00:48:05.340
that seems to pretty much verify

00:48:05.340 --> 00:48:07.050
that this kind of thing was happening.

00:48:07.050 --> 00:48:10.380
It's a furious massacre,

00:48:10.380 --> 00:48:15.380
and if the Jewish population
pre-1648 was 40,000,

00:48:15.810 --> 00:48:18.933
only about 21,000 seemed to survive.

00:48:20.040 --> 00:48:22.680
Many, 8,000, become refugees

00:48:22.680 --> 00:48:24.720
and are wandering across Europe.

00:48:24.720 --> 00:48:27.300
1,000 convert to save their lives,

00:48:27.300 --> 00:48:30.480
and 3,000 are taken
captive mainly by Tatars

00:48:30.480 --> 00:48:32.760
and sold in slave markets

00:48:32.760 --> 00:48:35.670
in far-flung places in the Ottoman Empire,

00:48:35.670 --> 00:48:38.700
often redeemed by the local
Jewish communities there,

00:48:38.700 --> 00:48:42.210
and, you know, it's an absolute shock

00:48:42.210 --> 00:48:45.183
to the Jewish sense of
security and stability.

00:48:46.170 --> 00:48:48.120
As a result, and I'm gonna finish here,

00:48:48.960 --> 00:48:51.480
as a result, you know,

00:48:51.480 --> 00:48:56.280
there's a kind of psychic trauma
to the Jewish collectivity

00:48:56.280 --> 00:48:58.980
that makes it easier

00:48:58.980 --> 00:49:03.750
for this false messiah,
Shabbetai Tzvi, to arise.

00:49:03.750 --> 00:49:04.890
You know, it's a little bit later,

00:49:04.890 --> 00:49:06.690
but he bases his whole career

00:49:06.690 --> 00:49:10.230
on vengeance for the 1648 massacres

00:49:10.230 --> 00:49:12.360
and managed to convince
Jews all over the world

00:49:12.360 --> 00:49:13.380
that he's the messiah,

00:49:13.380 --> 00:49:16.230
and they follow him, and they
sell off their possessions,

00:49:16.230 --> 00:49:18.810
and some move to the land of Israel

00:49:18.810 --> 00:49:20.853
convinced that the Messiah has come,

00:49:22.050 --> 00:49:24.600
but, you know, after that disappointment

00:49:24.600 --> 00:49:26.910
and throughout this period, really,

00:49:26.910 --> 00:49:28.500
Jewish communities managed

00:49:28.500 --> 00:49:31.590
to reconstitute themselves very quickly.

00:49:31.590 --> 00:49:33.930
We know that from the number of houses.

00:49:33.930 --> 00:49:36.933
The Jewish population
continues to increase,

00:49:37.770 --> 00:49:40.650
really significantly increase.

00:49:40.650 --> 00:49:42.360
How do we explain this

00:49:42.360 --> 00:49:44.670
if it was such a devastating massacre?

00:49:44.670 --> 00:49:48.660
It seems that the poor were
probably the main victims

00:49:48.660 --> 00:49:50.970
because they have fewer means of fleeing,

00:49:50.970 --> 00:49:54.033
you know, the Cossack armies.

00:49:55.260 --> 00:49:57.300
The wealthy are able to flee successfully,

00:49:57.300 --> 00:49:59.910
and they can come back and
reconstitute these towns,

00:49:59.910 --> 00:50:02.910
and that seems to be what
happened in this case,

00:50:02.910 --> 00:50:06.780
but look, this is a point in time

00:50:06.780 --> 00:50:10.830
when the system broke down,
when it didn't really work,

00:50:10.830 --> 00:50:14.520
but I just wanna end by saying

00:50:14.520 --> 00:50:17.700
that the system really
worked most of the time,

00:50:17.700 --> 00:50:20.040
that this was more the
exception than the rule.

00:50:20.040 --> 00:50:24.750
There was this kind of
economic-based symbiosis,

00:50:24.750 --> 00:50:28.830
really based on a relationship
with the Polish nobility,

00:50:28.830 --> 00:50:31.980
and it's really only with the
decline of the nobility itself

00:50:31.980 --> 00:50:33.870
towards the end of the 19th century

00:50:33.870 --> 00:50:36.030
that the system breaks down completely.

00:50:36.030 --> 00:50:39.150
That's when you're gonna
have the so-called pogroms,

00:50:39.150 --> 00:50:40.950
these anti-Jewish riots,

00:50:40.950 --> 00:50:44.040
you know, beginning the
1880s, and then 1903 to '06,

00:50:44.040 --> 00:50:48.093
and the worst being in 1919
and during the Holocaust.

00:50:49.050 --> 00:50:51.570
This system usually worked

00:50:51.570 --> 00:50:54.810
and usually kept Jewish
life in the Ukraine

00:50:54.810 --> 00:50:55.830
and the rest of Eastern Europe

00:50:55.830 --> 00:50:58.203
relatively secure and prosperous.

00:50:59.040 --> 00:51:00.642
Okay, thank you.

00:51:00.642 --> 00:51:03.642
(audience clapping)

00:51:07.870 --> 00:51:10.537
(pensive music)

